    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-16T10:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-16T10:41:00-05:00" n="909"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d909">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/459</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-16T17:00:00+01:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 17, 12.19 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2636. My 2452, May 3, 7 p.m., 1(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>). The Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs tells me that Germany has agreed to discuss the export of Dutch
                    gravel as an exchange basis for the import of German coal and iron. He also
                    stated that he expects the final exchange of notes in Berlin today which will
                    conclude the understanding in regard to the recent German demands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
